description.narrative: 4.1 Strengthened management and coordination mechanisms of the governmental institutions linked to the 1,000 days initiatives to accelerate the reduction of malnutrition in a healthy environment, including emergency situations., which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Community-Based Management Of Acute Malnutrition, Nutrition â€“ General, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Sanitation, Sanitation (Covid), Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition (Covid), Wash And Emergencies, Wash â€“ General, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By the end of 2019, women, girls and boys, particularly those in rural indigenous areas, access comprehensive package for health, nutrition and Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH), to guarantee the healthy growth and development, in particular during the child's first 1,000 days (from conception to 2 years of age), and to prevent and reduce chronic malnutrition and morbidity/ mortality.

description.narrative: UNICEF provided assistance to the Government of Guatemala with the implementation of the National Crusade for Nutrition, including the development for first time in the counry of a National Communication Strategy for Social and Behaviour Change.UNICEF supported the implementation of a baseline assessment (Houshold Survey) of the National Crusade to provide information for decision making, addressing the overall lack of timely data on health/nutrition, food availability, WASH, social protection, and social/behaviour change.Through the leaderhips of the nutrition and WASH clusters, UNICEF strengthened the coordination of partners around the Eta/Iota and COVID-19 related emergencies, and implemented the Nutrition Brigades strategy. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/01/2022
